commit.message:
Don't link any code objects into the fake DLLs

Fake DLLs contain no code and export no symbols, so passing any code
objects to the linker is entirely pointless.

This also fixes a meson warning about an extract_all_objects() change.
Fix meson warnings
Fix all shellcheck warnings
Add .gitignore
bootstrap: add nixos support

bootstrap: allow specifying distro via command line

NixOS does not make /etc/os-release available in the build environment,
so we need a different way to find out.
Rather than try to be clever, add a simple argument parser which accepts
a distro name.
bootstrap: fix shellcheck warnings
bump version to 0.10-devel
set version to v0.9-release

switch CI to winehq 6.0 packages

The current releases are binary incompatible with WINE v8.3, as that version
removed libwine, which all our releases link against.

We need to build with >=v5.7 in order to drop that dependency from the
resulting binaries.

Hence switch to the old stable v6.0 to build our releases. That fixes the
binary compatibility with >=v8.3, but unfortunately limits it to >=v5.7 at the
same time.

backup and restore the original d3d9.dll

General problem: if WINEPREFIX already has d3d9.dll and you installing Nine,
the old d3d9.dll will be deleted. After this change it will be stored as d3d9-nine.bak.

d3d9-nine: switch "win_updated" to LONG

InterlockedExchange wants a LONG*, give it one.
Fixes a -Wincompatible-pointer-types warning.

fix remaining -Wformat warnings

Just sprinkle some ugly casts.

common: sync debug functions from WINE

To get rid of -Wformat warnings.
ninewinecfg: Add Portuguese translation

switch CI to ubuntu 20.04

18.04 will be fully unsupported by 2023/04/01
Add note about older Intel gen4-7 graphics and Crocus
README: fix badge link
bump version to 0.9-devel
set version to v0.8-release

Required by tools/get_version.sh

build: add support to pass WINE[64|32]_LIBDIR

Older WINE versions ship a broken winegcc wrt multiarch library paths,
this can be used to work around it.

d3d9-nine: Update drawable pos when X drawable gets notify event

The notify event is sent whenever the drawable has change
of geometry, position or stack order.
Any such change can affect the result of get_drawable_offset,
thus we must call it again.
